single-stranded RNA and DNA sequences. Since NCD assembles into nucleocapsid-like particles with nucleic acids at the sample concentrations required for many ensemble techniques, such as circular dichroism or NMR spectroscopy [45,48], the 1:1 complex was probed at the very low concentrations accessible with single-molecule spectroscopy. nsFCS showed that the
