Best RB: Computational and theoretical advances in studies of intrinsically disordered proteins. Curr Opin Struct Biol 2017, 42:147-154 Excellent review of recent developments in applying theory and simulation to IDPs on different time-scales and length-scales that illustrates the
versatility in methods required for describing the properties of disordered proteins and the complementarity with experiments.
31. 
Bottaro S, Lindorff-Larsen K: Biophysical experiments and biomolecular simulations: a perfect match? Science 2018, 361:355-360 In this excellent review, the authors summarize recent progress in integrating molecular simulations with experiments, especially for generating ensembles and for validating and improving force fields, a powerful approach that has become essential for biophysical research at the molecular level.
