46. 
Holmstrom ED, Liu ZW, Nettels D, Best RB, Schuler B: Disordered RNA chaperones can enhance nucleic acid folding via local charge screening. Nat Commun 2019, 10
This study combines single-molecule FRET and coarse-grained simulations to elucidate the functional mechanism of a disordered viral RNA chaperone. The authors demonstrate that the positively charged IDP forms a disordered polyelectrolyte complex with single-stranded nucleic acids and facilitates the formation of compact nucleic acid conformations by acting as a flexible macromolecular counterion that locally screens repulsive electrostatic interactions with an efficiency equivalent to molar salt concentrations.
