74. 
Dignon GL, Zheng WW, Best RB, Kim YC, Mittal J: Relation between single-molecule properties and phase behavior of intrinsically disordered proteins. Proc Natl Acad Sci U S A 2018, 115:9929-9934 Using a coarse-grained model, the authors show that the single-chain properties and the condensed-phase interactions of IDPs are closely related. The results suggest that experiments performed in dilute conditions may be used to predict phase separation, which may also be applicable to polyelectrolyte complex coacervation.
